LiveIron !Kolibr1.86 Sun 23 Jul 2023 04:07:52 No.58232060 Report
Quoted By: >>58232383
>>58231997

>Anon's Friendship With a Gym Lioness
I really liked this story! The prose had some technical issues, but the story itself made it easy to overlook.
The way the relationship develops is nice. It's realistic and slow, and by the end I feel like they really do like each other. I was a little sad that things ended there, actually.
I'd be happy to read more about these two. Tali is really likeable, and you do really good descriptions when it counts.
In general, I'd suggest giving things a quick read-through before you publish it, just to catch the little bumps in the prose. It is greentext, but still.
Solid work.

>Smexy Time With a Lioness
I liked the sex with this one. Glad Will ended up with the biggest lioness -- got a thing for big cats, if you haven't noticed.
The setting itself kind of threw me for a loop. The anthros are presented as being as intelligent as humans, yet they're treated like animals (see the photography stuff at the very beginning and the mention of poachers).
I would have figured Aziza and her tribe would be a bit more hostile to Will if that were the case. It seems a bit /collared/, but then at the same time him being taken as the village babymaker is pretty /adhg/.
The prose itself was okay, but a lot of words were repeated close together. It's really noticeable during the sex, and kind of took away from it for me personally. Varying your word choice will help the flow of the story.
I'd also advise against completely typing out foreign dialogue. It adds to length for little gain, since the main character (Will) can't understand it, and therefore (most of us) can't either. The intro after he wakes up would be much shorter if their conversations in Swahili were summarized rather than written out.
Keep the stuff that Aziza says, though. Singular words and small phrases from a meaningful character are fine -- especially when they explain them.
It's a good start!
